25":"1225","1268":"1268","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1266":"1266","about 1225":"about 1225","1285":"1285","about 1266":"about 1266","after 1268":"after 1268","of,Derby,England":"Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","Bradley, Derbyshire, England":"Bradley, Derbyshire, England","Stretton en le Field,Derbyshire,England":"Stretton en le Field, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Derby, Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, England","Kniveton, Derbyshire, England":"Kniveton, Derbyshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Old German: Mighty battle maid"]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":64,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":73,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":108,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda was born in Derby, Derbyshire, England. She married Roger Stretton of Bradley about 1260, in Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died after 1268."},"et":{"–after 1268":"–pärast 1268","–1268":"–1268","1225–1266":"1225–1266","1245–1285":"1245–1285","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","Abt 1260":"umbes 1260","1225":"1225","1268":"1268","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1266":"1266","about 1225":"umbes 1225","1285":"1285","about 1266":"umbes 1266","after 1268":"pärast 1268","of,Derby,England":"Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bradley, Derbyshire, England":"Bradley, Derbyshire, England","Stretton en le Field,Derbyshire,England":"Stretton en le Field, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Derby, Derbyshire, England":"Derby, Derbyshire, England","Kniveton, Derbyshire, England":"Kniveton, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"–after 1268":"–1268 jälkeen","–1268":"–1268","1225–1266":"1225–1266","1245–1285":"1245–1285","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","Abt 1260":"noin 1260","1225":"1225","1268":"1268","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1266":"1266","about 1225":"noin 1225","1285":"1285","about 1266":"noin 1266","after 1268":"1268 jälkeen","of,Derby,England":"Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bradley, Derbyshire, England":"Bradley, Derbyshire, England","Stretton en le Field,Derbyshire,England":"Stretton en le Field, Leicestershire, Englan